Garlic

Allium sativum

Medicinal Plants
Author: Yash Shinde
Published: 26/11/2025
Read Time: 5 min read
Category: Medicinal Plants
Location: Pune

Description

Garlic (Lahsun) ek zameen ke andar ugne wala bulb wala paudha hai. Har bulb mein kai chhoti kaliyan (cloves) hoti hain. Garlic ka teekha taste aur strong smell uske medicinal sulfur compounds se aata hai sabse important Allicin.


Indian gharon mein garlic ko khane ke saath-saath ek natural medicine ki tarah bhi use kiya jata hai.

Ye infection se ladne, immunity badhane, BP control, cholesterol kam karne, pachan sudharne aur heart ko protect karne mein madad karta hai.


Medical studies ne dikhaya hai ki garlic antibacterial, antifungal, antiviral aur anti-inflammatory tarah kaam karta hai.

(References: Rahman K., Garlic and Health, Nutrition Journal; Rivlin R., Historical Perspective on Garlic, J Nutr.)


Medicinal Properties

Antibacterial antiviral antifungal anti-inflammatory antioxidant immune-boosting cardioprotective antihypertensive lipid-lowering antithrombotic (blood-thinning) digestive stimulant

Common Uses

  • Raw garlic for immunity
  • Garlic-honey for cough/cold
  • Garlic oil for earache (lukewarm & diluted)
  • Garlic paste (diluted) for fungal skin infections
  • Garlic in food for heart health
  • Garlic tablets/capsules for cholesterol
  • Garlic water for digestion
  • Garlic pickle for appetite stimulation

Local Names

Locality Local Name
Hindi
Marathi
Gujrati

Growing Information

Growing Conditions

Full sun, loose sandy-loam soil, well-drained soil, slightly acidic to neutral pH, cool climate start, avoid waterlogging, proper spacing between cloves

Water Requirements

Moderate moist soil needed during growth, reduce watering during bulb formation, no standing water.

Temperature Range

1225C ideal for sprouting and bulb formation; dislikes extreme heat.

Harvesting Tips

Harvest 34 months after planting Leaves turning yellow/brown indicate maturity Gently loosen soil and pull bulbs Cure/dry bulbs in shade 710 days Store in cool, dry place for long shelf life

Preparation Methods

Garlic Paste

Fresh cloves crushed; applied diluted with coconut oil for skin fungal issues.

Garlic Oil

Heat garlic in sesame/coconut oil; use for ear pain (warm, not hot).

Garlic Powder

Sun-dry cloves and grind; used in herbal mixes.

Garlic Honey

Mix crushed raw garlic with honey; used for sore throat & immunity.

Chemical Compounds

Allicin alliin ajoene diallyl disulfide diallyl trisulfide S-allyl cysteine sulfur compounds flavonoids selenium
